{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RogC18hVE3NvG2Auk1s2M1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the mongosh ping takes about 0.664 seconds right now - very close to the 1 second timeout. Under load or during startup, this could easily exceed 1 second.\n\nThe key issues with the current probe configuration:\n1. `timeoutSeconds: 1` - mongosh takes ~0.66s normally, but can easily exceed 1s under load, during startup, or when MongoDB is busy\n2. `failureThreshold: 2` for liveness - only 2 consecutive failures before the pod gets killed/restarted (very aggressive)\n3. The liveness probe has `initialDelaySeconds: 15` which might be too short if MongoDB takes longer to start up after a restart\n4. In a replica set scenario, during initialization or elections when MongoDB is under heavy load, the ping command will take even longer, and with the current aggressive thresholds, this creates a cascade of pod restarts\n\nThe fix should be increasing `timeoutSeconds` to 5 seconds, raising `failureThreshold` to 3-5 for liveness, and ensuring `initialDelaySeconds` gives MongoDB enough time to fully start.\n\nI should also check if the health user exists in MongoDB and consider using authenticated probes for better robustness.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":756,"cache_read_input_tokens":34873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":756},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"610c88d7-98b7-4dbd-8aae-45d3792d2ed5","uuid":"e9bcc1cc-0668-4e3a-9cb9-fe673f1ede46","request_id":"req_011Ccgd2Kru587s67abrHqxg"}
