{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JA9gy6QCV1Prk2vvCKNgr7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see from the logs that:\n1. The replica set is running with term 16 and primaryId 1 (so mongodb-replica-1 is currently the primary!)\n2. mongodb-replica-0 is a SECONDARY (state 2)\n3. The replica set is working but has had many elections (term 16 means 16 elections have happened, which is bad)\n\nThe log shows \"syncingTo\": \"mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\" which means replica-0 is syncing from replica-1 (the primary).\nThe high number of elections points directly to the probe configuration causing pod restarts. The ping command takes about 0.66 seconds, but with a 1-second timeout and a failureThreshold of 2, the probes are too aggressive and triggering unnecessary pod kills. I need to increase the timeout to 5 seconds and raise the failureThreshold to give the replica set more stability.\n\nI should also bump the initialDelaySeconds for the liveness probe to 30 seconds to give MongoDB time to fully start up. Since there's a dedicated health user with a secret, I'll use that for the probe instead of the default credentials.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5640,"cache_read_input_tokens":37267,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5640},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"610c88d7-98b7-4dbd-8aae-45d3792d2ed5","uuid":"f3604b66-1d81-4861-893c-223ddb4067ed","request_id":"req_011Ccgd4KKhhqNaY7HTFRD1T"}
