{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PkhaUn9imGwxQ94xL9xEH7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So neither the health user nor admin user can authenticate. This is strange. The passwords from the secrets might not match what's actually in MongoDB. Since the pods have been restarted many times and the persistent volumes might have the old data, maybe the users were never properly initialized, or the replica set initialization script ran before users were created, or there's a password mismatch.\n\nBut the important thing right now is that `db.adminCommand('ping')` DOES work without auth (it returned 1 earlier). So the probe doesn't need auth.\nThe real problem is the probe configuration itself—the one-second timeout is way too tight and the failure threshold is too aggressive. I need to patch the StatefulSet with more reasonable values: giving the readiness probe an initial delay of 10 seconds, checking every 10 seconds with a 5-second timeout and allowing 6 failures before marking it unhealthy, and for the liveness probe, starting after 30 seconds, checking every 20 seconds with a longer timeout.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":376,"cache_read_input_tokens":43486,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":376},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"610c88d7-98b7-4dbd-8aae-45d3792d2ed5","uuid":"3155b462-a404-4e27-a6a5-213bda5b805e","request_id":"req_011Ccgd5WGYtFNUXjLD7KyGZ"}
