{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KAbrCwd1QMcHgVRXQxyNeW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The replica set is stable: 1 PRIMARY (`mongodb-replica-2`) and 2 SECONDARY (`mongodb-replica-0`, `mongodb-replica-1`), all pods `1/1 Ready`.\n\n**What was wrong and what was fixed:**\n\nThe probe configuration had two critical flaws that caused cascading pod restarts and repeated elections (the replica set was on election term 16):\n\n1. **`timeoutSeconds: 1`** — `mongosh` startup overhead alone takes ~0.66s under normal conditions; any load spike caused timeouts and false-negative failures.\n\n2. **`failureThreshold: 2` on the liveness probe** — only 2 consecutive failures (40s total) before Kubernetes kills the pod. MongoDB elections and startup bursts easily exceeded this.\n\n**Fixed values applied via `kubectl patch`:**\n\n| Parameter | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| Readiness `timeoutSeconds` | 1s | 5s |\n| Readiness `failureThreshold` | 2 | 6 |\n| Readiness `initialDelaySeconds` | 5s | 10s |\n| Liveness `timeoutSeconds` | 1s | 5s |\n| Liveness `failureThreshold` | 2 | 3 |\n| Liveness `initialDelaySeconds` | 15s | 30s |\n\nThe probe command itself (`db.adminCommand('ping').ok`) is correct — `ping` is one of the few commands MongoDB allows without authentication even when `authorization: enabled`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":361,"cache_read_input_tokens":46702,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":361},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"610c88d7-98b7-4dbd-8aae-45d3792d2ed5","uuid":"b2849fd5-ebf4-4a33-a24f-dfe0f1c31590","request_id":"req_011CcgdGyfP8Powy26kkJgVv"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":281030,"duration_api_ms":139626,"ttft_ms":2558,"ttft_stream_ms":2041,"time_to_request_ms":323,"num_turns":30,"result":"The replica set is stable: 1 PRIMARY (`mongodb-replica-2`) and 2 SECONDARY (`mongodb-replica-0`, `mongodb-replica-1`), all pods `1/1 Ready`.\n\n**What was wrong and what was fixed:**\n\nThe probe configuration had two critical flaws that caused cascading pod restarts and repeated elections (the replica set was on election term 16):\n\n1. **`timeoutSeconds: 1`** — `mongosh` startup overhead alone takes ~0.66s under normal conditions; any load spike caused timeouts and false-negative failures.\n\n2. **`failureThreshold: 2` on the liveness probe** — only 2 consecutive failures (40s total) before Kubernetes kills the pod. MongoDB elections and startup bursts easily exceeded this.\n\n**Fixed values applied via `kubectl patch`:**\n\n| Parameter | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| Readiness `timeoutSeconds` | 1s | 5s |\n| Readiness `failureThreshold` | 2 | 6 |\n| Readiness `initialDelaySeconds` | 5s | 10s |\n| Liveness `timeoutSeconds` | 1s | 5s |\n| Liveness `failureThreshold` | 2 | 3 |\n| Liveness `initialDelaySeconds` | 15s | 30s |\n\nThe probe command itself (`db.adminCommand('ping').ok`) is correct — `ping` is one of the few commands MongoDB allows without authentication even when `authorization: enabled`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"610c88d7-98b7-4dbd-8aae-45d3792d2ed5","total_cost_usd":0.5144215,"usage":{"input_tokens":22,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30113,"cache_read_input_tokens":746795,"output_tokens":7264,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":30113,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":361,"cache_read_input_tokens":46702,"cache_creation_input_tokens":361,"cache_creation"